        <detaileddescription>
<para>It splits <computeroutput>xc</computeroutput> at the split point into two subcurves <computeroutput>xc1</computeroutput> and <computeroutput>xc2</computeroutput>, such that <computeroutput>p</computeroutput> is <computeroutput>xc1</computeroutput>&apos;s <emphasis>right</emphasis> endpoint and <computeroutput>xc2</computeroutput>&apos;s <emphasis>left</emphasis> endpoint. The direction of <computeroutput>xc</computeroutput> is preserved. That is, in case <computeroutput>xc</computeroutput> is directed from left to right, <computeroutput>p</computeroutput> becomes <computeroutput>xc1</computeroutput>&apos;s target and <computeroutput>c2</computeroutput>&apos;s source; otherwise, <computeroutput>p</computeroutput> becomes <computeroutput>xc2</computeroutput>&apos;s target and <computeroutput>xc1</computeroutput>&apos;s source. </para>        </detaileddescription>
